########To run locally using environment.yml (linux/mac/windows)########
1. From Anaconda Prompt (Windows) or terminal (Linux/Mac)

conda env create -f environment.yml
conda activate mintllm


2. Run Streamlit

streamlit run app.py

### alternative instructions using requirements.txt file ###

########To run locally (linux/mac)########

1. Create fresh conda environemnt

conda create -n mintllm python=3.10 -y
conda activate mintllm

2. Install dependencies

pip install -r requirements.txt

3. Run streamlit!

streamlit run app.py


########To run locally (windows)########

1. Open Anaconda Prompt

Click Start â†’ Anaconda Prompt (or open your terminal if conda is already on PATH).

All commands below should be typed in that window.

2. Create a fresh environment
conda create -n mintllm python=3.10 -y
conda activate mintllm


(This makes and activates an environment called mintllm.)

3. Install dependencies

Navigate to your project folder first, for example:

cd path\to\mint-llm-streamlit-scaffold-fixed


Then install:

pip install -r requirements.txt

4. Run Streamlit

Still in the project folder:

streamlit run app.py


This will launch Streamlit and open a browser tab (or give you a local URL to copy-paste).

